Document: VideoStreamPlayer
Path: godot/classes/class_videostreamplayer.rst
Summary: Defines the properties available for the VideoStreamPlayer node, including audio track selection, autoplay, buffering, audio bus, expansion, looping, pausing, playback speed, the video stream itself, playback position, and volume controls.

Properties
* audio_track (int): Index of the audio track to play. Default: 0
* autoplay (bool): If true, the video will start playing automatically when the scene loads. Default: false
* buffering_msec (int): The buffering time in milliseconds. Default: 500
* bus (StringName): The audio bus to which the video's audio will be routed. Default: "Master"
* expand (bool): If true, the video will expand to fill the available space. Default: false
* loop (bool): If true, the video will loop automatically when it finishes. Default: false
* paused (bool): If true, the video playback is paused. Default: false
* speed_scale (float): The playback speed multiplier. 1.0 is normal speed. Default: 1.0
* stream (VideoStream): The VideoStream resource to play.
* stream_position (float): The current playback position in seconds.
* volume (float): The volume of the video, ranging from 0.0 (silent) to 1.0 (full volume).
* volume_db (float): The volume of the video in decibels. Default: 0.0
---CHUNK---
Document: VideoStreamPlayer
Path: godot/classes/class_videostreamplayer.rst
Summary: This section details the methods and signals available for the VideoStreamPlayer class in Godot Engine.

Method: get_stream_length() → float
Returns the total length of the video stream in seconds.

Method: get_stream_name() → String
Returns the name of the video stream.

Method: get_video_texture() → Texture2D
Returns the current video frame as a Texture2D.

Method: is_playing() → bool
Returns true if the video stream is currently playing, false otherwise.

Method: play() → void
Starts or resumes playback of the video stream.

Method: stop() → void
Stops playback of the video stream.

Signal: finished()
Emitted when playback is finished.
